title: For Sale/Trade:  Guitars, drums, more for sale or trade for firearms
postcontent: I have three guitars (two of them electric), two amps, three fancy ukuleles, dual bass drum pedals, stands and more to trade for new/like new pistols and possibly revolvers. Maybe even an AR-15.My stuff is also for sale if you'd prefer a cash deal. Drop me a line, and we can discuss prices. One guitar is a 2014 orange Ibanez hollow-body. Another is a boutique guitar made by a small company in Florida called Fool; this model is the Fool Ignatz, with a distinctive hot rod stripe down its mahogany body. The third is a 3/4-size Takamine acoustic. One amp is a Line 6 combo amp. The other consists of an Orange Micro Terror head and two small cabinets; the full stack won't even reach your waist, but it'll blow your ears out. Two of the ukuleles are expensive, solid wood Lanikai models; the other is a less expensive Oscar Schmidt OU-4. The bass pedals are pricey ones by Crush. All of the above are like new, as I can't actually play any instruments. Oh, I also have an old, powered pedal board and about nine pedals, including a like new Dunlop Crybaby From Hell wah and an Electro-Harmonix Holy Grail. Come to think of it, I also have African drums: a djembe, a set of congas and a 4 1/2-foot-tall ngoma. I'm sure we can package things together to make a fair trade. Please do not flag my post, as someone did earlier. You can't mention guns on Craigslist, so this is about the only place for me to try to arrange a swap. I'm not a dealer; I'm just an obsessive collector with a short attention span, so I'm emptying my house of musical stuff. I'm a real guy paying a real mortgage in Edmond. I don't put my phone number in public ads, but if you email me I'll be happy to provide it.

postcontent: The CMR-206 Rail Master® is compact, yet powerful, universal green laser sight designed to fit rail-equipped pistols, rifles and shotguns. The laser sight fits onto virtually any firearm with a modern (M1913 Picatinny or Weaver-style) accessory rail. Ambidextrous control tabs allow the user to instantly activate or deactivate the laser. The human eye processes the color green more effectively than any other color, and Crimson Trace offers the brightest green laser allowed by law, (5mW peak, 515nm, Class 3R). The CMR-206 Rail Master boasts 2 hours of (constant) run time on a single 1/3N Lithium battery, and features a 5 minute auto shut-off for power conservation. The CMR-206 offers 3 modes of operation: Momentary, Strobe, and Constant-On. This allows the user to easily set their mode based on personal need or preference. The unit is quickly and easily user-installed in moments and can be painlessly transferred from firearm to firearm. The CMR-206 is securely fastened using Crimson Trace's Secure Lock Technology (SLT™).
